description:

description: The Westman Construction Company was hired to level a park and build and industrial complex in it's place. The possible destruction of a park brought unwanted attention of teenage protesters who were in favor of the park over pollution causing factories. The whole situation eventually escalated enough in front of Namor the Sub-Mariner which made him take an interest in the protesters plight. The current status of the company is unknown after Namor and the protesters gave Sam Westman the owner and founder of the company a change of heart.

deck: The Black Knights are an elite group of warriors that enforce the will of the Universal Church of Truth.
description: The Black Knights are the foot soldiers of religious zealots who worship the Magus within the Universal Church of Truth. The Black Knights have clashed with Adam Warlock and the Guardians of the Galaxy. The Black Knights infiltrated Earth and set up a base of operations in Colorado. They were eventually challenged and defeated by the Annihilators. The Black Knights have been led by different commanders such as General Egeus and Captain Autolycus but Autolycus lost his soul to the Soul Gem.
name: Black Knights

deck: The Mini-Gingers are miniature versions of the Gingerdead Man, that he made with the same batter he was made.
description:
The Mini-Gingers were made from the same batch of batter from which the Gingerdead Man was made. The Gingerdead Man made them himself. By working as a group, they can attack humans and by crawling into the mouth of a human, they can make sure they're eaten, placing that human under the control of the Gingerdead Man. They can also reform into a giant gingerbread man.

They were destroyed when, in their collected form of a giant gingerbread man, a cupcake full of firecrackers was stuffed in its mouth and exploded.
name: Mini-Gingers

description:
t is unknown why the Italian aerialists the Great Gambonnos joined the Circus of Crime, but they have been long standing members seemingly only missing their first appearance against the Hulk. They consider themselves to be the "Kings of the Trapeze", and they effectively use their acrobatic skills in tandem to cause confusion, but they were unable to best either Spider-Man or Daredevil.

The identical twins joined the Clown, Princess Python, and the Human Cannonball in the Masters of Menace, wanting to break from the Ringmaster and hoping for better success. However, when Spider-Man stopped their criminal endeavors, the returned to Ringmaster and the Circus of Crime.

description:
Origin

The Deluge is a fiercely xenophobic and traditionalist Atlantean terror cell, that tries to oppose Aquaman by attacking the surface world.

Creation

The Deluge was created by Aquaman writer Dan Abnett.

Major Story Arcs

The Drowning

The Deluge appeared during DC Rebirth and tried to attack Boston under the leadership of Corum Rath, with Atlantean fusion bombs and enslaved sea beasts. The were defeated by Aquaman before they could carry on their attack.

Some days later the USS Ponchartrain was attacked, with indications that it was the Deluge.

Later, in Atlantis Aquaman questions the imprisoned Corum Rath on whether it was the Deluge that carried this attack, but Corum Rath denies it.

Resources & Equipment

  • The Deluge are Atlanteans which grants them the standard superhuman abilities all Atlanteans share, including some degrees of superhuman strength, enhanced durability, enhanced senses and underwater adaptation.
  • The Deluge has access to Atlantean techology and weaponry such as Atlantean vehicles, fusion bombs, energy rifles and implants that allow them to enslave and control sea beasts.
  • The Deluge has captured and uses Atlantean sea beasts.
